.SS KEYPAD FUNCTIONS
.PP
The number pad on a standard keyboard and the arrow keys on a laptop
have two reporting or transmit modes.
Use one or the other of these functions to ensure predictable
keystroke strings from
.B get_keystroke
so you can respond appropriately.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc start_keyboard_transmit_mode
.cdef_voidfunc stop_keyboard_transmit_mode
.sp -1
.IP
As an example, in
.BR keyboard_transmit_mode ,
the END key transmits
.RB \(lq \(rsE[F \(rq
but in non-transmit mode, it is
.RB \(lq \(rsE0F \(rq.
.IP
